<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8243171>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Lateral pinnae of Cyrtomium remotipinnum and its related species showing venation and sori.—A. C. remotipinnum, Guangxi, JSL7088 (CSH).—B. C. shingianum, Guangxi, JSL7622 (CSH).—C. C. pachyphyllum, Guangxi, GXMI055962.—D. C. calcis, Guangxi, JSL3613 (CSH).—E. C. guizhouense, Guizhou, JSL8353 (CSH).—F. C. grossum, Guangxi, JSL7629A (CSH)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8243171/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8243173>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2.Cyrtomium remotipinnum.—A.Outside viewof the limestone mountain wherethe new species was discovered.—B. Habitat.— C. Individual plant, JSL3591 (CSH).—D. Spores, ZYB02710 (left, IBK), ML503 (top right, IBK), 23755 (bottom right, GXMI).—E. Abaxial view of portion of rachis with a pinna showing sori, JSL3591 (CSH).—F.Adaxial view of portion of rachis with a pinna, JSL3591 (CSH).—G. Scales from base of stipe, JSL3591 (CSH).—H. Lower portions of stipes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8243173/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8243181>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Geographical distributions of Cyrtomium remotipinnum (centers of rings) in Guangxi, China." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8243181/files/figure.png" ;
